    'The altar of burnt offering, the court of the tabernacle, and the oil for the lampstand.',
    'Instructions for the priestly garments: the ephod, breastplate with twelve stones, robe, and golden plate inscribed HOLINESS TO THE LORD.',
    'The consecration of Aaron and his sons. The daily offerings — two lambs, morning and evening.',
    'The altar of incense, the atonement money, the bronze laver, the anointing oil, and the incense recipe.',
    'Bezaleel and Aholiab appointed as master craftsmen. The Sabbath commandment reiterated. Moses receives the tablets written by God.',
    'The golden calf. While Moses is on Sinai, Aaron makes an idol. Moses descends, breaks the tablets, grinds the calf to powder. Three thousand die.',
    'Moses pleads for Israel. He asks to see God\'s glory. God passes by, proclaiming His name: merciful, gracious, longsuffering, and abundant in goodness and truth.',
    'The covenant is renewed. New tablets are cut. Moses\' face shines when he descends from the mountain.',
    'Moses assembles Israel and repeats the Sabbath command. Offerings are collected for the tabernacle.',
    'The people bring more than enough material. Bezaleel begins crafting the tabernacle components.',
    'The ark, mercy seat, table of shewbread, lampstand, altar of incense, and anointing oil are constructed.',
    'The altar of burnt offering, the laver, and the court of the tabernacle are constructed.',
    'An accounting of the materials used. The priestly garments are made exactly as commanded.',
    'The tabernacle is erected on the first day of the first month of the second year. Moses inspects and blesses the work.',
    'The glory of the LORD fills the tabernacle. The cloud covers it by day and fire by night. When the cloud moves, Israel moves.',
